column2: Fallout: A Post-Nuclear Role Playing Game [Done]

column7: Description

Elmindreda the Avatar must set out into the post apocalyptic wasteland surrounding Los Angeles to find a new water purification chip for her vault, and she would really appreciate it if people would stop blaming the apocalypse on her casting the Armageddon spell, thank you very much.

---------------------------------------------

Fallout: A Post-Nuclear Role Playing Game is a critically acclaimed RPG originally released in 1997 by Interplay. Fallout is set in 2161, long after a nuclear war has devastated an alternate retro-futuristic world, and those who survived unscathed did so in underground vaults.

---------------------------------------------

The series is best viewed from the playlist:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL1Be_cMfHOEdLP4q1Gk3_NEHA0bCR9NJo

---------------------------------------------
